    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen you use omni-complete (`<Ctrl-x>` + `<Ctrl-o>`) and then show documentation, the omni-complete pop-up overlaps with the documentation. Which leaves no choice but to leave auto-completion and retry. I've tried a number of options such as `anchor_bias` and `relative` but nothing seems to improve this.\n\nHere's a demonstration\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c391c84-c1ce-47fd-83ed-42989342df42\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUsing this file:\n`reproduction.lua`\n```lua\nvim.bo.filetype = \"lua\"\n\nvim.lsp.start({\n    name = \"lua-language-server\",\n    cmd = { \"lua-language-server\" },\n    root_dir = vim.fn.getcwd(),\n})\n\nvim.keymap.set(\n    \"i\",\n    \"<C-k>\",\n    function()\n        vim.lsp.buf.hover({anchor_bias=\"below\"}) -- NOTE: Or other options here\n    end,\n    { silent = true }\n)\n```\n\n- Load neovim with the file: `nvim -u reproduction.lua`\n- Make a `foo.lua` file\n- Start typing `vim.api.nvim_get_current`\n- Enter omni-complete with `<Ctrl-x>` + `<Ctrl-o>`\n- Now try to show documentation with `<Ctrl+k>`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen `vim.lsp.buf.hover()` runs, it should be aware of other Vim-native possible floating windows or visual elements and choose a better position for the documentation. Usually to the right of the auto-completion is a good spot. Or, if there isn't enough room to the right, the documentation could display above the currently-written line. As a last resort if none of those are viable and we can't display both the omni-complete menu + documentation at once, the documentation floating window could pop-up on top the omni-complete menu (obscuring the omni-complete menu instead of what's happening currently, where the omni-complete menu is always on top).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1929+gf4f60f6a19\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10, WSL\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nCompiled from-source",
